				I've been saying we need to take this guy out since he first opened his yap.  This is one of those times a smart bomb needs to "go rogue" and "accidently" blow up whatever facility he's saying in, mosque or not.  I know there are religious/political conotations but it's not like we wont just rebuild the @#%$ for them.  
<br />

<br />
Al Sadr was originaly happy about the ousting of the Saddam regime.  Of course, all he wanted to do was replace the dictatorship with a traditional theocracy (with himself in a position of major power) and as soon as the US quit bowing to his increasing demands, raised a group of armed rabble and started shooting @#%$ up.  
<br />

<br />
Now that his %@$# is shot, he wants to sing the peace talks song because hes suddenly aware of his own mortality.  He may sing the praises of Allah, but he is a materialist who is just looking to climb the rungs of power and he cant do that if hes dead.  If the US/Iraq govornment is smart they will tell him to go @#%$ himself and that its time to put up or shut up.  Unconditionaly surrender of himself, to include standing trial for the murder he is being accused of, and the total disarming of his rabble.  No more deals, no more compromise.
<br />

<br />
I'd tell him "You have 72 hours to surrender and disarm your men, after that, we're coming in.  Women, children and men not interested in dying have 48 hours to leave the city.  They will be made as comfortable as possible for the duration of the seige.  Anyone still in the combat area will be considered hostile.  They can surrender or die.  We will be conducting a house to house search.  All firearms will be confiscated and destroyed.  Anyone firing on coalition forces from ANY location will be killed.  If you chose to use a mosque or other holy site as protetion, it will be bombed or shelled to rubble and we will feed your carcass to pigs.  The clock is ticking."<br />
